subSubSection.paragraph:
Each series of teeth moderately large, blunt and granular. Maxilla and inter maxillary teeth are continuous (
Fig 3
). Intermaxillary teeth with 3–4 rows of teeth mixed with both blunted and granular teeth. Maxilla with 1–4 rows of teeth mixed with blunt and granular teeth.. Teeth unequal in size; and blunted teeth are variable in size. Vomer with 1–3 rows in patch that extends posteriorly to mid–eye with blunt teeth from snout tip to middle of vomerine patch and granular teeth towards posterior end; maxillary and intermaxillary teeth patches continuous (
Fig.3
), without gap or suture between patches. Myorhabdoi absent. Vertebrae: 9–10 predorsal; 46–49 preanal; 61–66 precaudal; 146–149 total.
